Author:
Vol / Page: 190
Edition:
Quote: Soilage and silage: The wise dairyman will provide sufficient soilage (green-feed-producing crops) and silage to make good all possible shortage of pasture in summer or winter. Soilage and silage enable the dairyman to maintain the maximum flow of milk at the minimum cost of production, regardless of season. in the event of summer or autumn soilage crops (enumerated above) in part not being required for green feed, they can be made into ensilage ...
